# New Swift Package

When creating a local Swift package:
- Create it in `local packages/<PackageName>/`.
- Choose one template: `templates/Package.logic.swift` or `templates/Package.view.swift`.
- Replace every `[name]` placeholder in `Package.swift`.
- Keep package entries alphabetized in the project explorer.
- Add new package targets to `Biker.xcodeproj`.
- Ask only if package type or project-specific structure is unclear.